.SH "VERSION"
.IX Header "VERSION"
version 6.017
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
This plugin tries to compensate for the stupid crap that turns up in your
working copy, removing it before it gets into your dist and screws everything
up.
.PP
In your \fIdist.ini\fR:
.PP
.Vb 1
\&  [PruneCruft]
.Ve
.PP
If you would like to exclude certain exclusions, use the \f(CW\*(C`except\*(C'\fR option (it
can be specified multiple times):
.PP
.Vb 3
\&  [PruneCruft]
\&  except = \e.gitignore
\&  except = t/.*/\e.keep$
.Ve
.PP
